observations.recommendation:
The Consultant on Computer Programming Systems in coordination with the Municipal Accountant finally resolve the issue on the generation of financial reports such as Subsidiary Ledgers/Schedules so as to address this recurring audit observation;

The Municipal Accountant seriously consider availing the “e-NGAS” accounting system developed by the Commission; and

The Municipal Accountant submit timely the requested ledgers, once available, to the Audit Team for evaluation.

Municipal Accountant to:

Reconcile the balances of these accounts and prepare necessary adjusting entries to correct the abnormal balances;

Provide disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements as to the details of the abnormal balances and the history thereof.

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials to:

Issue demand letters to these accountable officials for the immediate liquidation of these cash advances; 


Initiate the write-off of these dormant unliquidated cash advances subject to the guidelines outlined in COA Circular No. 2016-005.

Municipal Accountant to reconcile the differences between the tax receivable accounts against their corresponding deferred tax accounts;
Municipal Accountant to give a justification as to the particulars of the unrecorded receipt and adjust accordingly the Special Education Tax account; and
Municipal Treasurer to ensure that total collections for each tax be equal.

We recommended and the Management agreed, through the Municipal Treasurer:
Refrain from granting cash advances to the Disbursing Officer for payments of bonuses and other personnel benefits of the Municipal officials and employees and instead be paid to their respective payroll ATM bank accounts;
Make representation with the bank to resolve the issue on frequent unavailability of cash in ATMs; and
Institute and adopt a sound system of internal control in safeguarding the agency’s assets, particularly cash;

We recommended that Management:
Submit to the Audit Team an authority from the Local Sanggunian for opening and maintaining savings account of the Municipality with the LBP, otherwise instruct the Municipal Treasurer to immediately close this account and transfer the funds to the Municipality’s main depository accounts;
Require the Municipal Accountant to make a Journal Entry Voucher to record the savings account balance of ₱30,508.90 in the books;
Immediately implement the programs/projects/activities in which such accounts were set-up in order to fully utilize the available resources and to avoid these accounts of becoming dormant; and
Revisit the purpose of opening these current and savings accounts and take appropriate actions in accordance with the above-stated provisions.

Based on the following audit observations, we recommend the following:

The Municipal Mayor to instruct the Municipal Treasurer in enforcing more efficient and effective administration and collection of real property and special education taxes so as to lessen the tax receivable account balances; 

The Municipal Accountant to reconcile the differences between the tax receivable accounts against their corresponding deferred tax accounts; 

The Municipal Accountant to give a justification as to the particulars of the unrecorded receipt and adjust accordingly the Special Education Tax account; and 

The Municipal Treasurer to ensure that total collections for each tax be equal.

